The paper discusses the use of multiple modalities (facial expression, speech, and car signals) for detecting distracted driving behavior, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions feature analysis and machine learning techniques, which are common in the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SD), natural language processing (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG).
